#note the esses are now gone which means that it's going to be significantly harder for him to bingo on the right side of the board. the only play that can really wipe me out is a bingo from the P so I thought it made sense to take out that lane and flip over as many tiles as possible as well. the only real alternatives that I see are TOKING at 7H or GOWK through the W, but I think POKING takes care of the most volatile lane. this is reflected by the sim - POKING drops noah's bingo percentage the most. combined with the turnover I think that has to make it the best play.
>Noah: ENZ B6 ZE.N +35 355
>Magra: DEINTTT J6 TIN +15 314
#note trying to take care of the most dangerous remaining bingo line...however, quackle disagrees and says that his bingo chances actually go up after TIN. instead, it suggests TOT as a more defensive play that achieves the same things. I guess it blocks the O too. the BROW-N hook isn't too dangerous I guess. on the other hand, TIN does score some points which is nice in case a freak play ensues.
